# Attendance Tracker Backend

Node.js + Express backend for the Attendance Tracker Meet add-on. Deployed on Google Cloud Run.

For the full architecture overview see the [top-level README](../README.md).

---

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/attendance?conferenceId=xxx` | Bearer JWT (optional) | Fetches participants from the Meet REST API. Uses service account delegation if configured for the tenant, otherwise the user's OAuth token. |
| POST | `/api/save-to-sheets` | Bearer JWT | Creates (or appends to) the user's per-Drive spreadsheet and writes the attendance report. |
| GET | `/api/calendar-attendees?meetingCode=xxx` | Bearer JWT | Looks up the calendar event matching the active meeting and returns the invited attendees. Returns empty list if the user didn't grant calendar scope. |
| POST | `/api/oauth/exchange` | _none_ | Swaps an auth code for a session JWT + persists the refresh token in Firestore. |
| POST | `/api/oauth/revoke` | Bearer JWT | Signs the user out and revokes the refresh token. |
| GET | `/api/admin/stats` | Bearer JWT | Tenant-scoped install + usage stats. Derives the tenant set from the union of explicit tenant docs and unique user domains. |
| GET | `/api/admin/all-users` | Bearer JWT (super admin only) | Aggregates users across every tenant via a Firestore collection group query. |
| GET | `/api/admin/insights` | Bearer JWT (super admin only) | Activation funnel, retention cohorts, top orgs, churned users, daily meeting volume. |
| POST | `/api/admin/install` | _none (Marketplace webhook)_ | Marketplace install hook. |
| POST | `/api/admin/uninstall` | _none (Marketplace webhook)_ | Marketplace uninstall hook. |
| POST | `/api/admin/verify-delegation` | Bearer JWT | Tests whether domain-wide delegation works for the given admin email and stores the config. |
| GET | `/health` | _none_ | Health check. |

All `/api/*` routes (except `/api/oauth/*` and the Marketplace webhooks) run through:
1. `requestId` -- correlation IDs in logs
2. `apiLimiter` -- 60 req/min per IP
3. `auth` -- validates the session JWT, refreshes the Google access token if needed, attaches `req.user`

The OAuth routes use a stricter limiter (10 req/min).

