## Notes

- **Conference ID:** The Meet add-on SDK returns `meetingCode` (e.g. `abc-defg-hij`). The Meet REST API uses this to look up `conferenceRecords`, which are only created once a meeting is live and may have a short delay. The frontend handles the "no record yet" case gracefully.
- **Tokens:** Refresh tokens are encrypted at rest in Firestore with AES-256-GCM keyed off `SESSION_SECRET`. Don't rotate `SESSION_SECRET` without re-OAuthing every user.
- **Domain mismatch fallback:** If the service account's impersonation email is on a different domain than the signed-in user, the backend skips the service account and uses the user's own OAuth token. This is how the add-on works for any Workspace domain without admin setup.
- **Implicit tenant docs:** Firestore doesn't auto-create the parent doc when you write to a subcollection. Historically, users existed under `tenants/{domain}/users/*` with no `tenants/{domain}` doc. `upsertUser` now creates the parent on first signup; admin endpoints union the tenants collection with unique user domains as a safety net for legacy data.
